    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
        <para>The V Ref circuit is a 5 &#177; .5 volt power supply from the ECM that provides power to the three wire
            engine and vehicle sensors and provides a benchmark or reference voltage for the ECM.
        </para>
        <para>There are three separate VRef circuits in this system.</para>
        <para>VRef B --For Chassis Sensors</para>
        <para>VRef C --For Body Builder Sensors</para>
        <para>VRef D --For Engine Sensors</para>
    </svcproc>
